alert.note: Alert for Eastern Alachua; Gilchrist; Western Alachua (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.senderName: NWS Jacksonville (Northeast Florida and Southeast Georgia)
info.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 11 at 2:01AM EST by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Gilchrist and southwestern Alachua Counties through 230 AM EST... At 201 AM EST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm capable of producing a landspout 7 miles southeast of Trenton, moving northeast at 25 mph. HAZARD...Landspouts and winds around 40 mph. SOURCE...Radar indicated. IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects. Locations impacted include... Gainesville, Alachua, Archer, University Of Florida and Newberry. LANDSPOUT...POSSIBLE MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH
info.instruction: If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building. Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.
